<br>
Because, the roleplay prefered server keeps away some raiders who dont dig too deeply into the rules.  If the server was merely called No-Drop, the upper end guilds would have A LOT more competition.  <br>
<br>
The Roleplaying prefered tag, to an extent, protects them.  Im sure that might brissle some, and its an opinion, not something that can be proven.  Even so, I would be hard pressd to acknowledge anyone that didnt accept the idea that the RP prefered tag has helped, if nothing else in the begining.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>its more about the fact that sometimes we just don't have the available classes, for whatever reason, to do the things we want to do<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, were it my place I would try real hard to get things going from within, before going to the outside world.  To me, it seems like buying your way to the top.  Your problems can be solved without going off the server to recruite, it would just be more time consuming.<br>
<br>
That's just me though and to be honest, the WHY isnt really important.<br>
<br>
I can understand and accept that FnF feels they need to recruite from outside of this server.  Im sure they are doing it with the intention of helping themselves, and not harming others.<br>
<br>
But<br>
<br>
There are many of us that still feel that it does.  People feel that the risk posed to the server is greater then the benefit for a few people.  Is that selfish?  It most certainly is.  It is just as selfish as wanting transfers in order to tackle higher content.<br>
<br>
Selfish.. self servering... bad terms to be labled with, but fitting to all parties involved in this, myself included.  Even so, for myself at least, I feel that my selfish action helps the community more then it hurts them... and the differing opinion harms more then it helps.<br>
